name: rtoml

A fast TOML library for python implemented in rust.

raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  version: 0.13.0

package:
  name: rtoml
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/r/rtoml/rtoml-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 974522c887b47abc0bb62ee8ae9e44d3a0c2cdac9d60ba0ed01c5a40df0ea424

build:
  number: 1
  script:
    - cargo-bundle-licenses --format yaml --output THIRDPARTY.yml
    - ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation

requirements:
  build:
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ compiler('rust') }}
    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
    - cargo-bundle-licenses
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - maturin >=1,<2
  host:
    - maturin >=1,<2
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - python

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - rtoml
      pip_check: true
  - files:
      source:
        - example.py
        - tests
    requirements:
      run:
        - coverage
        - dirty-equals
        - pytest
        - pytest-speed
    script:
      - coverage run --source rtoml --branch -m pytest -vv --tb=long -k "not datetime_invalid"
      - coverage report --show-missing --skip-covered --fail-under=100

about:
  license: MIT
  license_file:
    - LICENSE
    - THIRDPARTY.yml
  summary: A fast TOML library for python implemented in rust.
  homepage: https://github.com/samuelcolvin/rtoml

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - thewchan
